   "source": [
    "## File Handling\n",
    "In Python, you can handle files using built-in functions. Here are some common operations:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "411dae50",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Teacher: Why are you late, raghu?\n",
      "\n",
      "Raghu: Because of the sign\n",
      "\n",
      "Teacher: What sign?\n",
      "\n",
      "Raghu: The one that says \"School Ahead, Go slow\"\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "f=open(\"funny.txt\",\"r\")\n",
    "\n",
    "for line in f:\n",
    "    print(line)\n",
    "f.close()\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "d4037a20",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Teacher: Why are you late, raghu?\n",
      "\n",
      "Raghu: Because of the sign\n",
      "\n",
      "Teacher: What sign?\n",
      "\n",
      "Raghu: The one that says \"School Ahead, Go slow\"\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "with open(\"funny.txt\",\"r\") as f:\n",
    "    for line in f:\n",
